  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>All @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-rules.JournalEntry.MQixQwPAnbjydC5D.JournalEntryPage.fRctuS2C1P30zjAO]{abjuration spells} on all class lists are treated as being on the @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-rules.JournalEntry.vaLYevRxKe8mAvdE.JournalEntryPage.MNWLud81msaiZukw]{wizard spell list} for you, and you can choose them when picking wizard spells. You can use abjuration spell scrolls as if they are wizard spell scrolls.</p><p></p><p><em>This only applies to spells on one of the class spell lists. Eg. no wizard can choose @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-class-features.Item.u7aPgi0U1YedIg3K]{Divine Smite}, because it is a class feature and not on any spell list.</em></p>",
